<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<bibRefCitation author="Romero Garcia, AT" journalOrPublisher="Ruizia" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 160" refId="B30" refString="Romero Garcia, AT, Blanca Lopez, G, Morales Torres, C, 1988a. Revision del genero Agrostis L. (Poaceae) en la peninsula Iberica. Ruizia 7: 1 - 160" title="Revision del genero Agrostis L. (Poaceae) en la peninsula Iberica." volume="7" year="1988 a">
Romero 
<normalizedToken originalValue="García">Garcia</normalizedToken>
et al. (1988a)
</bibRefCitation>
provide a key to differentiate the two subspecies. The typical subspecies has ligules as long or longer than wide with acute apices, conduplicate leaf blades that recurve at anthesis, and shorter lemmas 0.5-0.8 mm long whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="P.M.Peterson, K.Romaschenko, R.J.Soreng &amp; S.P.Sylvester, 2020" authorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Quintanar, Soreng &amp; Sylvester" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Quintanar, Soreng &amp; Sylvester" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostula truncatula subsp. durieui" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="truncatula" subSpecies="durieui">Agrostula truncatula subsp. durieui</taxonomicName>
has ligules wider than long with truncate apices, flat, rarely conduplicate leaf blades that do not recurve at anthesis, and longer lemmas (0.7-)0.9-1(-1.2) mm long. 
<bibRefCitation author="Portal, R" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Linnean Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B24" refString="Portal, R, 2009. Agrostis de France. (privately published) Imprimerie Jeanne-d'Arc." title="Agrostis de France. (privately published) Imprimerie Jeanne-d'Arc." year="2009">Portal (2009)</bibRefCitation>
treated subsp. 
<taxonomicName authority="P.M.Peterson, K.Romaschenko, R.J.Soreng &amp; S.P.Sylvester, 2020" authorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Quintanar, Soreng &amp; Sylvester" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Quintanar, Soreng &amp; Sylvester" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. durieui" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="truncatula" subSpecies="durieui">durieui</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis durieui" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="durieui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Agrostis durieui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for France, and did not recognize 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. truncatula" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. truncatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as being in France.
</paragraph>
